<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-23T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/139: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Bahia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bahia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-23T15:00:00-03:00">October 23, 1930—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:46 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Battle expected at Algoinhas. Rumored that Algoinhas was captured this
                            morning. British cruiser here. German cruiser outside. No news of <hi rend="italic">Pensacola.</hi></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>